Q)write a Java stream program, Given a list of lists, flatten it into a single list?

ğŸŒ´Ans) let's break it down

ğŸ’step 1) convert the list of list to stream

ğŸ’step 2) call flatMap() with list::stream

ğŸ’step 3) call Collectors.toList to get all results list.

ğŸŒ´Example:
ğŸ‘‡

List<List<Integer>> listOfLists = Arrays.asList(
 Arrays.asList(1, 2, 3),
 Arrays.asList(4, 5),
 Arrays.asList(6, 7, 8, 9)
);

List<Integer> flattenedList = listOfLists.stream()
 .flatMap(List::stream)
 .collect(Collectors.toList());
System.out.println(flattenedList);

ğŸ’ğŸ‘‰Output: [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8, 9]